President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. L. Preston Bryant, Jr. will serve as Chair of the National Capital Planning Commission. Mohamed A. El-Erian will serve as Chair of the President's Global Development Council. Richard C. Blum, Sylvia Mathews Burwell, Esther Duflo, Sarah Beardsley Degnan Kambou, James M. Manyika, William K. Reilly, Steven Schwager, Smita Singh, and Todd A. Fisher will also serve as members of the President's Global Development Council. Additionally, Robert A. Sherman, Andrea Lavin Solow, and Michael Ashley Stein will serve as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council.